## 7.1 Favorite APIs (User-web) — Prompt Pattern (MUST)

**When implementing new favorite/bookmark APIs for logged-in users, follow this exact prompt-style rule:**

“For waterb_backend favorite APIs, never trust `ESNTL_ID` from client input. Resolve the current user from Spring Security (`LoginVO.uniqId`) in the Service layer, then write/delete favorites by `(ESNTL_ID, TARGET_ID)`. Request DTO must contain only business target keys (e.g. `proId`), and server-owned identity fields (`esntlId`) must be set on the server only.”

**MUST:**

- Use authenticated user identity from `SecurityContextHolder` (`LoginVO.getUniqId()`), in Service.
- Ignore or overwrite any client-provided `esntlId` field (if present for backward compatibility).
- Keep favorite endpoints resource-style (e.g. `POST /api/user/.../favorite`, `DELETE /api/user/.../favorite/{targetId}`).
- Use server identity consistently in Mapper parameters (`ESNTL_ID` + target key).
- Return `401` (or project-standard auth error response) when login identity is missing.

**MUST NOT:**

- Do **not** accept ownership decisions from frontend identity payloads (`esntlId`, `uniqId`).
- Do **not** put identity resolution or authorization branching in Controller.
- Do **not** write Mapper SQL that uses only target key without `ESNTL_ID` for user-owned favorites.

```java
// ✅ GOOD – server resolves ESNTL_ID from authenticated principal
String esntlId = getCurrentUserUniqId();
if (esntlId == null || esntlId.isBlank()) {
    response.setResult("40");
    response.setMessage("로그인이 필요합니다.");
    return response;
}
FavoriteCommand command = new FavoriteCommand();
command.setTargetId(request.getTargetId().trim());
command.setEsntlId(esntlId.trim());
favoriteDAO.deleteByUserAndTarget(command);
favoriteDAO.insertByUserAndTarget(command);
```

```java
// ❌ BAD – trusting client identity
FavoriteCommand command = new FavoriteCommand();
command.setTargetId(request.getTargetId());
command.setEsntlId(request.getEsntlId()); // client-controlled identity, forbidden
favoriteDAO.insertByUserAndTarget(command);
```

```xml
<!-- ✅ GOOD – user-scoped delete/insert -->
<delete id="deleteByUserAndTarget" parameterType="FavoriteCommand">
    DELETE FROM ARTMARK
     WHERE ESNTL_ID = #{esntlId}
       AND TARGET_ID = #{targetId}
</delete>
```

